profile_positions.description:
Leading all the activities, within Vopak LNG scope, related to the acquisition and start up of a new offshore FSRU-based LNG terminal. Including:
- overseeing all related activities in the commercial, legal, HR, operational and IT domains;
- supporting the negotiation and acquisition process of the FSRU (Floating Storage and Regasification Unit) resulting in a new Joint Venture partnership;
- developing and starting up the local Joint Venture organization in Hong Kong;
- setting up the integrated management system incl. all it's documentation in line with ISO9001 and ISO14001
- hiring & building the 17 FTE local Operations & Maintenance team;
- facilitating any (future) cooperation with key stakeholders in the project.

Two year management traineeship program.

Second assignment,  position at the Global Operations department.
- Project manager; 
- Responsible for migrating our safety incident management to a new IT -system. Including, global implementation and change management;
- Investigating methods to reduce consumption & costs of Energy & Utilities by studying innovative technologies, new business models, renewable energies and industrial energy management & monitoring methods. 

First assignment, position at Customer Service department until March 2017.
- Account manager for several large industrial & trader accounts at the Vopak Rotterdam Botlek terminals;
- Managing several performance improvement projects;
- Leading a project in order to improve collaboration with third parties service-providers.

Change Management consultancy firm
- Executing research regarding business development opportunities;
- Advised & collaborated with the consultants to support business development opportunities.

- Analyzed and succesfully developed a plan to improve the company's NPI (new product introduction) process in its indirect distribution channels, collaborating with all stakeholders in this process such as product development, marketing communication, sales, and the distribution network;
- Conducted marketing activities targeting distributors in the EMEA region;
- Kept track of and reported the department's monthly KPI's (Key Performance Indicators).

- Executed a feasibility study for the company's expansion into Europe
Business development activities:
- Identified, generated, and followed up on warm and cold leads in Shanghai city and the Greater Shanghai area; 
- Built up and maintained customer relationships with customers from different nationalities and attended networking events;
- Negotiated and closed contracts;
- Trained local employees sales' skills, business etiquette.
